<br>
I know it's not the 1950's and men no longer &quot;do the right thing&quot; i.e. marry a woman whom they've impregnated.  Also the marriage ratio is way low and the divorce rate is way high.<br>
<br>
I'm not old at all, quite young, but I wish it were still the days when people met, got married AND THEN had sex and kids, that's what it's for you know.<br>
<br>
If you get involved with a single mom, subconciously you'll feel pangs of resentment towards: the kid for encroaching on your relationship with the woman; the kid not being your own flesh and blood; the father for not taking responsibility ... etc  These are natural feelings.  Also the child may feel resentment towards you for the same exact reasons listed above.<br>
<br>
You're over 25 you need to be more mature about how you approach women anyway.  You need to start thinking in terms of relationships more than just knocking boots.  Trust me if you don't, you'll look up and be 40 or more and most likely lonely.  I understand that you meet attractive women and like them.  That's how it's supposed to be.  That's the first step.  Attraction -&gt; relationship -&gt; marriage [ a christian word, you can use any other word you like here ] -&gt; children [ this is how you live forever, or didn't you know ]<br>
<br>
Relationships are emotional.  Girls are emotional.  Boys are emotional.  Adding an extranious child in your would be relationship only adds to your feelings.  I know my parameters and I walk away from those situations immediately.  Don't play with the females emotions, nor the child's.<br>
<br>
Now lastly, don't create such a situation yourself.  If you're serious about  a woman, you should never go in thinking that divorce can get you out of a bad situation.  With this in mind then, you should make a good sound decision of whether you really want to marry someone.  Flimsy reasons for getting married should be thrown out.  Infatuation isn't a good reason either to get married.<br>
<br>
I'm the only child of a ... basically single mother [ father died before i could remember and they divorced before that ] single parents aren't a family unit.  The child needs the mother and father right there so that their development is perfect, so that they may observe closely, so that they can get from each sex what each has to teach, so that they can observe a sound relationship between a man and woman.<br>
<br>
I wish you all well.  Love yourselves.  Love your children.  Love your significant others. <p><table width="350" border="0"><tr><td width="144"><div align="center"><img src="http://www.geraldfield.com/nadinesplace/calvinquiz/spiff.gif" width="142" height="125" align="absmiddle"></div></td><td><div align="center"><b><font size="3">You are Spaceman Spiff!</font></b><br><font size="2">Zounds! You are the intrepid Spaceman Spiff, the engaging explorer ensconsed in an unending universe of exotic and evil extraterrestrials! You're brave, but you should give that dictionary a rest.<br><font size="1">Take the <a href="http://www.geraldfield.com/cgi-bin/unofficial/quizzes/sfesurvey.cgi?whatcalvinareyou" target="_blank">What Calvin are You? Quiz</a> by <a href="mailto:contessina_2000@yahoo.com">contessina_2000@yahoo.com</a>!</font></font></div></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizzoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izzoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 922<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/12/02 11:14:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1607.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/fatbastarddance.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Godless</span><hr size=1> In that case, I wish it was still Chinese Ming dynasty times (1300s to 1600s roughly) where men could have multiple concubines (legally recognized sexual and social partners in addition to the wife) who virtually beckoned to their every wish. And I'm sure Bill Clinton wished he was a Ming dynasty emperor (some where known to have as many as 150+ concubines at any one time). However, we don't always get what we want... <p><b>
