<br>
Also, people who want kids should not marry people that don't want kids.  That's just a divorce waiting to happen.<br>
<br>
I have also encountered women that don't want to have babies because of what it could do to their figures!  A guy I know told me that his brother was married to a woman and she got pregant.  She did not want to have kids because of what it would do to her figure.  Well, we don't always get what we want and she ended up becoming pregant, despite precautions.  He was pro-life and she was pro-choice.  She wanted an abortion.  He didn't want her to.  She got one anyhow.  They got a divorce over it.  Remember what I said earlier about marrying someone with the same religious/political beliefs?  Those two should have never married in the first place.  Regarding the thing about preserving their figures, it seems like a rather shallow reason to me, but I suppose it is their privelege.  I personally can't understand it unless the woman's career is dependent on her looks (model, actress, etc.).  If I were married and wanted to have kids and my wife did not because of her figure, I would wonder just who she wanted to preserve her figure for, because it apparently would not be me.<br>
